<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="429" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="35.[124,1332,1596,2576]" pageId="35" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[126,480,2309,2338]" pageId="35" pageNumber="429">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List (as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Woodman &amp; Timm" authorityYear="1993" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Cryptotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="35" pageNumber="429" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="colombiana">C. colombiana</taxonomicName>
). There are no major threats to Colombian Small-eared Shrews, and they can withstand some habitat destruction and alteration, although their distribution is restricted and experiences high rates of habitat loss. Virtually nothing is known ofits ecology, and additional research is needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
